Synopsis

The Crown follows the reign of Queen Elizabeth II from her wedding in 1947 to the present day. The series chronicles the political, social, and cultural events that have shaped the second half of the 20th century.

First aired in November 2016, The Crown has been critically acclaimed for its acting, writing, directing, and production values. The series has won numerous awards, including two Golden Globes, three Primetime Emmy Awards, and two British Academy Television Awards.

In July 2022, Netflix announced that the fifth season of The Crown would be its final season. The sixth season will cover the events of the 1990s, including the death of Princess Diana and the marriage of Prince William and Catherine Middleton.
